(thirdQuint)Phase II Study of Clofarabine in Pediatric Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia (ALL).

 This is a non-randomized, open label, Phase II study of Clofarabine in pediatric patients with refractory or relapsed acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL).

 Eligible patients must be in second or subsequent relapse or be refractory.

 Forty eligible patients will be enrolled in a Fleming 2-stage sequential study design in order to better assess the efficacy and safety of clofarabine in this patient population.

